Is that just counting this year?

55
00:15:09,420 --> 00:15:11,153
Look, five is nothing, okay?

56
00:15:11,273 --> 00:15:15,241
Henry, my roommate,
he told me that if anyone asks,

57
00:15:15,494 --> 00:15:16,844
to just round up.

58
00:15:17,215 --> 00:15:19,630
- Apparently five is total loserville.
- Really?

59
00:15:21,428 --> 00:15:22,883
The truth is I get bored.

60
00:15:24,007 --> 00:15:26,470
Three months,
that's as long as they ever last.

61
00:15:28,546 --> 00:15:31,132
Chloe was nine months,

62
00:15:32,069 --> 00:15:33,323
but, I mean...

63
00:15:34,194 --> 00:15:37,731
The last two didn't really count
'cause she was away and I was away.

64
00:15:38,741 --> 00:15:40,191
And anyway, I was...

65
00:15:40,862 --> 00:15:43,012
I was cheating on her with Maggie.

66
00:15:43,291 --> 00:15:45,857
You remember Maggie,
right, the violin player?

67
00:15:46,421 --> 00:15:47,871
You were cheating...

68
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,910
You were cheating on Chloe with Maggie?

69
00:15:53,404 --> 00:15:56,333
What can I say, man?
There was a lot of beer involved.

70
00:16:06,085 --> 00:16:08,012
Have you spoken to Rosie lately?

71
00:16:08,408 --> 00:16:09,471
About what?

72
00:16:15,805 --> 00:16:17,855
I think you should know that...

73
00:16:20,651 --> 00:16:22,985
There's been some stuff
going on between...

74
00:16:24,568 --> 00:16:26,593
Between your mother and me.

75
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:29,065
I thought maybe...

76
00:16:30,256 --> 00:16:32,119
Maybe Rosie had mentioned it.

77
00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:33,787
What kind of stuff?

78
00:16:36,336 --> 00:16:37,408
I don't know.

79
00:16:40,144 --> 00:16:41,994
We've been having problems.

80
00:16:43,123 --> 00:16:44,798
You are always having problems.

81
00:16:45,572 --> 00:16:47,134
Really?
You think so?

82
00:16:47,999 --> 00:16:49,349
What else is new?

83
00:16:50,565 --> 00:16:52,306
This stuff is new...

84
00:16:56,369 --> 00:17:00,188
It's something
that we really have to work on.

85
00:17:03,995 --> 00:17:05,133
It sounds big.

86
00:17:06,626 --> 00:17:09,376
You didn't sleep with someone else,
did you?

87
00:17:11,968 --> 00:17:12,968
Did mom?

88
00:17:18,770 --> 00:17:20,209
Is mom having an affair?

89
00:17:23,136 --> 00:17:24,273
No, she's not.

90
00:17:27,569 --> 00:17:28,900
It's me, actually.

91
00:17:32,845 --> 00:17:34,097
I met somebody...

92
00:17:34,494 --> 00:17:37,412
But we're not having an affair.

93
00:17:47,723 --> 00:17:48,937
Do I know her?

94
00:17:49,271 --> 00:17:50,621
I don't think so.

95
00:17:55,338 --> 00:17:56,862
Is she a patient?

96
00:17:59,105 --> 00:18:00,340
She's not.

97
00:18:08,928 --> 00:18:12,386
Are you happy or are you miserable
about it? I can't tell.

98
00:18:13,674 --> 00:18:14,793
I'm both.

99
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:18,488
I know it sounds crazy,
but there's a part of me

100
00:18:18,912 --> 00:18:20,051
that wishes

101
00:18:20,856 --> 00:18:23,706
I didn't feel the way I do,
and then there's...

102
00:18:24,029 --> 00:18:25,482
Are you in love with her?

103
00:18:29,095 --> 00:18:31,272
I don't know.
I'm not sure.

104
00:18:38,353 --> 00:18:39,788
Are you splitting up?

105
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:45,154
We're trying to work it out
at the moment.

106
00:18:54,779 --> 00:18:56,535
Maybe it's for the best.

107
00:18:57,761 --> 00:19:00,601
You've been married a long time,
longer than I've been alive.

108
00:19:00,963 --> 00:19:02,295
That's pretty good.

109
00:19:04,037 --> 00:19:06,148
I'd say you're entitled
to have some fun.

110
00:19:06,732 --> 00:19:08,358
Didn't I say that to you?

111
00:19:10,092 --> 00:19:12,571
- When?
- When you first went to school.

112
00:19:13,301 --> 00:19:14,980
About Chloe, I said:

113
00:19:15,274 --> 00:19:18,792
"You're 18 years of age
and you're entitled to have some fun."

114
00:19:18,928 --> 00:19:20,883
- Remember that?
- So what?

115
00:19:21,003 --> 00:19:23,040
I told you.
You were probably right.

116
00:19:23,282 --> 00:19:24,998
Why don't you take your own advice?

117
00:19:25,118 --> 00:19:27,868
But that's a completely
different situation.

118
00:19:28,141 --> 00:19:30,839
You were just a kid.
I've been married for over 20 years.

119
00:19:31,234 --> 00:19:32,484
It's ridiculous.

120
00:19:32,912 --> 00:19:35,115
You don't know
what you're talking about.

121
00:19:35,235 --> 00:19:37,299
I'm sorry.
What do you want me to say?

122
00:19:37,419 --> 00:19:39,222
"You're a total asshole shithead?"

123
00:19:39,483 --> 00:19:41,742
Maybe you should say
I'm a total asshole, a shithead,

124
00:19:41,862 --> 00:19:43,769
because that's what you're thinking.

125
00:19:46,223 --> 00:19:48,589
Whatever, dad.
This is stupid.

126
00:19:52,648 --> 00:19:54,862
I know when my parents split up...

127
00:19:55,342 --> 00:19:57,132
I had to struggle for a long time.

128
00:19:57,252 --> 00:20:00,609
- In some ways, I'm not even sure...
- Well, I'm not you, dad.

129
00:20:01,319 --> 00:20:03,080
What do you want me to say?

130
00:20:03,384 --> 00:20:04,822
"Please don't leave?"

131
00:20:04,942 --> 00:20:07,377
"What are you doing to our family?"

132
00:20:08,053 --> 00:20:10,349
Or maybe you just want me to stop you?

133
00:20:10,995 --> 00:20:12,212
I get it, okay?

134
00:20:12,332 --> 00:20:14,591
I get why you would want to be
with someone else.

135
00:20:14,835 --> 00:20:18,014
I can understand how after 23 years
of marriage you could get tired.

136
00:20:18,134 --> 00:20:21,517
All the nagging
and all those long-suffering...

137
00:20:21,695 --> 00:20:25,013
Silent-but-deadly looks
she gives you when you let her down.

138
00:20:25,186 --> 00:20:27,168
She does it to Rosie, to me...

139
00:20:27,438 --> 00:20:29,665
Everything from some tone
you're using in your voice

140
00:20:29,785 --> 00:20:33,582
- to leaving a wet towel on the bed.
- They're issues that you have with her.

141
00:20:33,702 --> 00:20:35,652
They're not necessarily mine.

142
00:20:36,245 --> 00:20:37,989
You think it's so different with you?

143
00:20:38,387 --> 00:20:42,080
You don't feel like
she's always disappointed or something?

144
00:20:43,108 --> 00:20:44,898
The woman has got a martyr complex.

145
00:20:45,018 --> 00:20:47,368
I don't know how you can deal with it.

146
00:20:48,185 --> 00:20:49,188
Martyr?

147
00:20:50,134 --> 00:20:53,877
That woman put her career
on hold for 15 years for you.

148
00:20:54,308 --> 00:20:57,315
She took you to baseball games,
to guitar lessons.

149
00:20:57,450 --> 00:20:59,177
She was always there for you.

150
00:21:00,557 --> 00:21:04,319
She's entitled to some kind of gratitude
along the line, don't you think?

151
00:21:06,483 --> 00:21:07,795
I know.

152
00:21:10,118 --> 00:21:11,700
I didn't mean to...

153
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:16,239
- Whatever.
- Don't say that word to me.

154
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:18,560
"Whatever."
God, I hate that word.

155
00:21:19,397 --> 00:21:21,741
- It's such a cop-out.
- What do you want me to say?

156
00:21:21,997 --> 00:21:24,580
I want you to have a little
respect for your mother.

157
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,288
Is that too much to ask?

158
00:21:26,549 --> 00:21:29,875
I do, but is it so impossible
that I could be genuinely on your side?

159
00:21:30,118 --> 00:21:34,044
But you don't have to take sides, Ian.
I'm not asking you to take sides.

160
00:21:39,552 --> 00:21:41,261
Maybe it wasn't fair of me to...

161
00:21:41,970 --> 00:21:44,639
- This is a lot for you to deal with.
- That's a cop-out, okay?

162
00:21:45,043 --> 00:21:46,641
You can't have it both ways.

163
00:21:46,901 --> 00:21:50,033
I'm old enough to tell,
but I'm too young to understand it?

164
00:21:50,153 --> 00:21:53,066
- Don't patronize me.
- I don't mean to patronize you.

165
00:21:56,727 --> 00:21:59,813
Something like this
takes a long time to process.

166
00:22:00,148 --> 00:22:03,348
I know you have these feelings.
I just want us to be able...

167
00:22:03,468 --> 00:22:05,285
To talk about them, you know?

168
00:22:07,371 --> 00:22:08,821
This isn't about me.

169
00:22:09,396 --> 00:22:12,500
It's not about what I feel
or why I feel it. It's about you.

170
00:22:13,355 --> 00:22:14,937
What are you gonna do?

171
00:22:15,496 --> 00:22:16,846
What do you want?


